# Dropdown Menu library (PEP Web)

The **Dropdown menu** preview page (`/preview/dropdown-menu`) is the source of truth for menu list-item compositions and Field Multi shells that open a menu.

## Page structure (`DropdownMenuPage.tsx`)

| Section | Purpose | Registry |
|--------|---------|----------|
| **Notes** | shadcn Dropdown Menu + Figma Menu Item styles | Page copy |
| **Library → Menu items** | One card per list-item composition | `section: 'menu-item'`, `tier: 'library'` |
| **Library → Field compositions** | Multi / Multi Image / Multi Avatar | `section: 'field-composition'` |
| **Pending** | New styles under review | `tier: 'pending'` |

## Figma Menu Item styles (`2740:597`)

| Figma `style` | Registry id | Compose with |
|---------------|-------------|--------------|
| Text | `text` | `DropdownMenuItem` (+ shortcut / arrow) |
| LeadingCheck | `leading-check` | `DropdownMenuItem` + `CheckIcon` / spacer |
| TrailingCheck | `trailing-check` | `DropdownMenuCheckboxItem` |
| Icon | `icon` | `DropdownMenuItem` + leading icon |
| Icon+TrailingCheck | `icon-trailing-check` | `DropdownMenuCheckboxItem` + leading icon |

## Adding a new list style (mandatory)

1. Add a row to `DROPDOWN_MENU_STYLE_ROWS` in `dropdown-menu-registry.ts` (`tier: 'pending'`).
2. Add a `StylePreview` case on `DropdownMenuPage.tsx` (always-visible `MenuSurface` preferred).
3. Promote to `tier: 'library'` only when the user asks.

## Layout rules

1. Before coding a menu, pick a **Library** row by Figma style / behaviour.
2. Reuse shadcn primitives from `@/components/ui/dropdown-menu` — do not fork item chrome per page.
3. Field Multi shells: `@/components/field-multi-selects` + `LibraryField` (same as Field §2).

## Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `pep-web/src/data/dropdown-menu-registry.ts` | Library / Pending catalog |
| `pep-web/src/pages/DropdownMenuPage.tsx` | Catalog UI + previews |
| `pep-web/src/components/ui/dropdown-menu.tsx` | Primitives |
| `pep-web/src/components/field-multi-selects.tsx` | Field Multi shells |

## Anti-patterns

- Burying every style inside one interactive mega-menu (hard to scan / manage).
- Page-local item markup that is not a registry row.
- Duplicating Multi field chrome instead of `field-multi-selects`.
